==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ephod
<hw>Eph"od</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Heb. '⟦emac⟧ph⟦omac⟧d,
fr. <ets>'⟦amac⟧phad</ets> to put on.]</ety> <fld>(Jew. Antiq.)</fld>
<def>A part of the sacerdotal habit among Jews, being a covering for the
back and breast, held together on the shoulders by two clasps or
brooches of onyx stones set in gold, and fastened by a girdle of the
same stuff as the ephod. The ephod for the priests was of plain linen;
that for the high priest was richly embroidered in colors. The
breastplate of the high priest was worn upon the ephod in front.</def>
<rj><au>Exodus xxviii. 6-12.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ephor</ent>⟦br⟧
